ous people devalue themselves. Do not expect to be uplifted, but do prepare to be astonished.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aMayaszMexicozChiapasvFiction. 4aAmerican Studies : Indigenous Studies. 4aCultural Studies : Postcolonial Studies. 4aGeneral Interest : Fiction. 4aLatin American, Caribbean, and Latinx Studies : Latin American Studies. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / General.2bisacsh1 aArias, Arturo, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aRuiz, Mikel, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSell, Sean S., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSellschopp, Alejandro Aldana, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertSUNY Press eBook Package 2023z978311149193640uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978143849298840uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781438492988423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781438492988/original  a978-3-11-149193-6  SUNY Press eBook Package 2023b2023  aGBV-deGruyter-alles